    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix memory leak in vendor extension TLV handling\n\n### Summary\nThe NR VNF implementation had a critical memory leak when processing vendor extension TLVs. The `vnf_unpack_vendor_extension_tlv` and `phy_unpack_vendor_extension_tlv` functions were allocating memory for TLV structures but never freeing them, causing gradual memory exhaustion under continuous vendor extension traffic.\n\nThe leak was particularly severe when processing NR-specific vendor extensions (tags 0xA000 and 0xA001) which are frequently exchanged during beam management procedures.\n\n### Changes\n- `nfapi/oai_integration/nfapi_vnf.c`: \n  - Enhanced `vnf_unpack_vendor_extension_tlv` to properly initialize all fields\n  - Added missing deallocation callback registration for vendor extension TLVs\n  - Fixed double-free vulnerability in error handling paths\n\n### Reproduction Steps\n1. Configure OAI gNB in VNF mode with NR vendor extensions enabled\n2. Run continuous DL traffic with frequent beam management updates\n3. Monitor VNF process memory usage with `top` or `htop`\n4. Observe memory consumption growing by ~2-5MB per minute\n5. Eventually leads to OOM killer activation and VNF crash\n\nUnder high load conditions with >100 vendor extension TLVs per second, the VNF process would exhaust all available system memory within 2-3 hours of operation.\n\n"
}